EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 232300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND E ACROSS THE N SEA
BUT WITH A TROUGH OF LOW PRESSURE SLOW MOV THROUGH THE EERN ENGLISH CHANNEL.
THE RIDGE IS EXP TO PERSIST THROUGH TUESDAY AS THE TROUGH SLWY WEAKENS BUT
FCST TO DECLINE DURING WEDNESDAY AS LOW PRESSURE MOVS N TO THE W OF THE BRITISH
ISLES AND FRONTAL TROUGHS MOV SLWY E THROUGH WERN PARTS OF THE UK CURRENT
INDICATIONS ARE THEN FOR THE FRONTAL TROUGHS TO TRANSFER E INTO THE N SEA
DURING THURSDAY. WINDS WILL STRENGTHEN N OF 58 N ON TUESDAY EVENING WITH
NEAR GALE TO GALE FORCE WINDS LIKELY IN SEA AREA FAIR ISLE ON WEDNESDAY MORNING
BUT THESE THEN EXP TO MOD BY THURSDAY MORNING. FURTHER GALES MAY THEN DEVELOP
IN THE FAR NE OF THE CULLERCOATS ARE DURING THURSDAY
